    <note>Li(2) Chudao [7273] Direct descendant of Tang Taizong. During the Five Dynasties, an ancestor, Cheng [3477], was a Later Liang dynasty envoy to Min and moved his branch of the clan from Kaifeng, Chenliu xian to Fuzhou, Lianjiang xian. Cheng was the great great grandfather of Chudao's father, Yuqing(3) [3554]. Yuqing(b) used yin to establish this family branch (qijia) of the lineage and probably was the  person who moved the family to Futang xian. His wife was Gong(2) Shi. Chudao was Chuhou's [7272] younger brother, Chuchang's [7271] brother, Zhuan's [3489] uncle, Mixun's [1062] and Mida's [1063] granduncle, and Gong(2) Zongyuan's [7114] son-in-law. Fujian TZ, 147.23b; Zhang Lei, WJ, 60.1a-4a; Wang Anshi, WJ, 94.971-2. CBD, 2, 1028-9.</note>
